1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,828
Look at Mom and Dad.

3
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:39,622
They're still so sweet with each other.

4
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,791
That's what you should dream about.

5
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,168
Like Mom.

6
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:44,711
All that love stuff!

7
00:00:44,794 --> 00:00:48,298
The only thing on my mind
is for you to finish your studies.

8
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:55,305
I'm sorry.

9
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:00,560
What are you doing here?
Did you follow me?

10
00:01:00,643 --> 00:01:01,895
I'll return your money.

11
00:01:58,034 --> 00:01:59,911
-Mikoy.
-What story?

12
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,747
-Mikoy.
-Nothing to tell you.

13
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:14,008
When it comes to sex,

14
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:15,426
you tell me nothing?

15
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,678
Sex?

16
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:18,888
No, no, no, no.

17
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,056
Nothing like that.

18
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:56,676
What is that?

19
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:30,389
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

20
00:06:36,687 --> 00:06:39,524
My name
is Special Agent Alexandria Cortez.

21
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:44,195
If you're thinking

22
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:47,240
that this will be one of those
romantic love stories,

23
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:50,368
then you're mistaken.

24
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:03,714
So, let's start by getting to know

25
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:05,716
who the demon is that we are facing.

26
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,387
This is Viktor Valtrovi.

27
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:19,105
But don't be fooled.

28
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:20,064
Because the truth is,

29
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:23,443
Viktor Valtrovi is the head
of the Moraviano Syndicate.

30
00:07:27,113 --> 00:07:28,781
But some people say

31
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:31,659
it was originally part of Cosa Nostra.

32
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,220
Do you like goulash?

33
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:52,430
My goulash is very good.

34
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:53,848
I'll give you goulash for free!

35
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:29,884
This is Congressman Celestino Salazar.

36
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:32,303
He was one of the first to investigate

37
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:35,139
the entry of foreign syndicates
into the country.

38
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:44,815
And clearly, it's a warning
by Viktor and the Moravianos

39
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:47,652
to anyone who wants to interfere
with their operations.

40
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:57,995
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

41
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:03,834
He's Michael D. Pinagpala.

42
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,545
Also known as Mikoy.

43
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:11,551
Chiara frequented the restaurant
where Mikoy works.

44
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,678
That's where they first met.

45
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:23,187
At first, we believed
their meeting was just accidental

46
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:26,315
and that they didn't really have
a deeper connection.

47
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:39,912
If I'm being honest,

48
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:43,457
I can't really blame Chiara
if she falls for Mikoy.

49
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:44,875
He's a good man.

50
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:50,965
He exudes an Enrique Gil vibe.

51
00:09:51,048 --> 00:09:54,010
If Enrique Gil is a bit worn out by life.

52
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:57,054
Though if I am really being honest,

53
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:59,015
Piolo Pascual is more likely my type.

54
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:02,977
But it doesn't matter
if he's Enrique Gil or Papa P.

55
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,604
What matters

56
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,772
is that we now have a way to infiltrate

57
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,567
one of the most dangerous
syndicates in the world.

58
00:10:13,821 --> 00:10:16,490
So Mikoy will be the key to our mission

59
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:20,369
in bringing down
this massive criminal syndicate.

60
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,040
It's cold.

61
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,417
Here's some coffee.

62
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:31,922
Is this really the only CCTV
that you can hack?

63
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:39,263
So he doesn't even have
CCTV inside his houses.

64
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:41,641
If there's no CCTV,
then we have nothing to hack.

65
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,100
Why, what happened?

66
00:10:43,934 --> 00:10:45,311
Viktor is making a move.

67
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:46,520
He already had Mikoy kidnapped.

68
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:47,772
Huh?

69
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:48,814
What the heck! Why?

70
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:50,483
He probably discovered that

71
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:52,693
his daughter Chiara and Mikoy
are starting to like each other.

72
00:10:52,777 --> 00:10:54,612
And now he has taken Mikoy
inside the house.

73
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:26,143
Actually, why am I even asking questions
when I already know the answer?

74
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:27,603
Yes.

75
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:30,856
It is very likely that he will intimidate
Mikoy to stay away from his daughter.

76
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:51,252
Maybe this will be the last time
we ever see this Mikoy.

77
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:11,730
I have no bad intentions toward her.

78
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:28,873
-Yes.
-No! No! No!

79
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:50,436
-Do not fool me, boy!
-Please! Please! Please!

80
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:01,989
I'm sorry.

81
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:04,658
Sorry, sir.

82
00:13:04,742 --> 00:13:05,743
Viktor!

83
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,580
In Tagalog… What are you doing, huh?!

84
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,670
What are you doing? About to release him?

85
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:18,506
Release him?!

86
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,758
Don't lie to me! I know what you're doing!

87
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:23,093
You're trying to scare him
for our daughter!

88
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:25,179
She will be angry!

89
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:27,556
She will not talk to you for a year!
Would you like that?

90
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:29,683
Of course not!

91
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:31,018
Bad guy!

92
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:32,686
-Bad boy! Bad boy!
-Ouch!

93
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:42,655
By the way, I'm Donabel.

94
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:43,948
I am Chiara's mother.

95
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:49,703
The undisputed beauty queen
of Mabalacat, Pampanga!

96
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:51,247
Your turn.

97
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,206
Introduce yourself.

98
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:02,383
But with a Filipino heart
because of my wife.

99
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:05,844
And the global handsome guy,

100
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:08,389
Czech Charmer of Europe!

101
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:13,978
I'm sorry.

102
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:24,446
Sorry about my husband.
That's really how he is.

103
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:25,906
He does foolish things!

104
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,659
But he's a nice person, sometimes.

105
00:14:28,742 --> 00:14:29,577
Right.

106
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,036
I am nice,

107
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,080
but only slightly.

108
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:38,210
Anyway, you were reported to us
by one of Chiara's bodyguards.

109
00:14:38,294 --> 00:14:40,004
And I was very happy.

110
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:42,381
My daughter finally has a date!

111
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:46,135
Also, a fellow countryman, of course!

112
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:56,729
Where are you from?

113
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:00,691
Mikoy.

114
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:03,193
Mikoy? Well, I'm a beauty queen.

115
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:04,445
Charmer.

116
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:08,908
-You…
-I'm Mikoy Pinagpala.

117
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,579
Bisdak…

118
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:14,788
There…

119
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:17,333
Heartthrob?

120
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:19,543
Of…

121
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,087
-Cebu?!
-Yes!

122
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:24,423
-City!
-That's it!

123
00:15:24,506 --> 00:15:26,258
Very good! Because of that,

124
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:27,760
you have to stay here for dinner.

125
00:15:27,843 --> 00:15:29,803
So we can get to know each other, right?

126
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,138
-It's fine.
-Sweetheart?

127
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:32,222
Perfect!

128
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:34,433
We have adobo for dinner!

129
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:36,602
Okay, okay.

130
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:38,646
She is Donabel Dimaunahan.

131
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,314
From Mabalacat, Pampanga.

132
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,441
She met Viktor

133
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:46,070
when Donabel worked
as the caregiver of Viktor's mother.

134
00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:51,867
And they were blessed with one child.

135
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,869
And her name is Chiara.

136
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,621
-I'm so happy!
-What is this?

137
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,458
Oh, perfect, dear! Here…

138
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,168
We invited him for dinner.

139
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:03,545
So we can all get to know each other.

140
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:06,048
Why is Mikoy here?

141
00:16:19,561 --> 00:16:21,522
And who told you that he is my boyfriend?

142
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:23,607
How did you even know that I know him?

143
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:30,489
How many times do I have to say

144
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:32,908
that I don't want you
interfering in my life?

145
00:16:34,868 --> 00:16:36,829
Dad, stop!

146
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:37,871
Okay? Stop.

147
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:45,421
Let's go.

148
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:47,589
Let's go.

149
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:57,766
Now you see what I have to go through
when it comes to my parents.

150
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,351
That's how they are.

151
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:02,688
They always keep
watching me wherever I go.

152
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:05,441
Whatever I do in my life, they interfere.

153
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,067
That's what I've been telling you.

154
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:10,404
Alex! Alex!

155
00:17:11,321 --> 00:17:12,448
Alex, Mikoy is out.

156
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,866
He's with Chiara.

157
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:16,827
Are you even listening?

158
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,370
That's what I've been telling you.

159
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:22,041
That's why I feel suffocated
by the life they want for me.

160
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:24,001
Why didn't you tell me?

161
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:26,962
-That you're from a rich family.
-Huh?

162
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:28,172
Why?

163
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:30,257
How is that relevant, huh?

164
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:34,636
Does something have to change
just because my status in life is higher?

165
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:37,473
I'm just a waiter, Chiara.

166
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:39,099
And you?

167
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:41,310
This?

168
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:45,731
Our worlds are completely different.

169
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:49,443
And do you think I care?

170
00:17:51,278 --> 00:17:52,863
You just don't understand.

171
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:55,783
Then make me understand.

172
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:02,790
And I think you like me, too.
So what's the problem?

173
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:06,794
I just want to go home.

174
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,464
This day has been too long already.

175
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:15,677
Okay fine, I'll have someone drive you.

176
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:16,887
No need.

177
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:19,890
Well, at least let me call you a cab.

178
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:21,225
Chiara.

179
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:25,479
I can manage on my own.

180
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,941
But thank you.

181
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:32,402
Okay, fine. If that's what you want.

182
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,487
You need strategy!

183
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:16,989
-Be careful with that.
-This way first.

184
00:19:17,072 --> 00:19:18,866
-It's brand new.
-Here. Let's put it down here.

185
00:19:18,949 --> 00:19:20,033
Oh, it's Mikoy!

186
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:22,536
Son, why did you call?

187
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:24,121
Wait a minute.

188
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:25,747
It's already night there, right?

189
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:27,457
Why aren't you resting yet?

190
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:31,420
I told you to be careful with it, Mario!

191
00:19:31,503 --> 00:19:32,921
-That's very expensive, right?
-It's nothing!

192
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:35,090
It's just his knee.
The knee just gave out.

193
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:36,800
-That's what I'm saying.
-Just the knee.

194
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:37,718
Hey, son.

195
00:19:37,801 --> 00:19:42,514
Do you remember
you gave us some extra money?

196
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:45,225
So, your Dad and I decided

197
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:48,228
to buy a new couch.

198
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:51,565
Well, our couch is already torn apart.

199
00:19:51,648 --> 00:19:53,400
It's really old, son.

200
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,611
Wait, I'll show you.

201
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:57,321
Everybody!

202
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:59,031
Say hello to Mikoy!

203
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:02,492
Live via satellite
from the City of Prague!

204
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:04,161
Mikoy!

205
00:20:04,244 --> 00:20:05,287
How are you, son?

206
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:07,164
Hello, Mikoy! Come home!
We miss you already!

207
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:09,666
Send us some booze!

208
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,043
Or some Czech girls!

209
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:11,960
Hey!

210
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,837
-That's it!
-Wait a sec!

211
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:15,839
Czech girls?

212
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,342
Well, son, why did you call?

213
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:19,843
Nothing, Mom.

214
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:20,969
Just checking in.

215
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:23,472
Nothing has changed here
in the Philippines.

216
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:25,515
You know, it's still chaotic.

217
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:27,434
You know, son,

218
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:30,020
a Congressman was killed here.

219
00:20:30,103 --> 00:20:34,358
He's Partylist Congressman Salazar.

220
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:36,568
He was killed, son.

221
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:40,030
Wait a minute.
Why am I giving you bad news?

222
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:41,657
How are you doing there?

223
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,283
I'm okay, Mom.

224
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:44,785
Nothing's wrong.

225
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:46,495
Are you really okay?

226
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:49,498
I'm fine, Mom.

227
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,965
Mikoy, turn on your screen.

228
00:20:58,048 --> 00:20:59,549
I want to see you.

229
00:21:09,726 --> 00:21:10,936
What's the problem?

230
00:21:11,019 --> 00:21:13,063
Who's messing with you?
Who's fighting with you?

231
00:21:13,146 --> 00:21:14,439
Do you need backup?

232
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,650
Tell me, I'll deal with them!

233
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:17,567
Who is it?!

234
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:19,444
No one, Mom.

235
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:20,904
I'm really okay.

236
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:22,864
Mikoy!

237
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:26,076
Don't lie to your mom.

238
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:27,494
Because first of all,

239
00:21:28,078 --> 00:21:31,290
there's high resolution
and high pixel density

240
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:33,208
in my phone's screen.

241
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:37,713
So, I can see in your eyes
if you have a problem.

242
00:21:38,213 --> 00:21:39,506
Well, Mom,

243
00:21:39,589 --> 00:21:42,509
I just got into a complicated situation.

244
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:44,761
You just admitted it!

245
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:47,264
Son.

246
00:21:47,848 --> 00:21:51,393
How hard is your complicated situation?

247
00:21:52,394 --> 00:21:53,812
It's about a girl, Mom.

248
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:56,106
We're in big trouble!

249
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:57,607
There's nothing we can do.

250
00:21:58,108 --> 00:21:59,693
If you got her pregnant,

251
00:22:00,944 --> 00:22:02,738
you have to take responsibility!

252
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:03,780
Oh, no!

253
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:05,365
Pregnant?

254
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:06,825
Who got pregnant?

255
00:22:06,908 --> 00:22:08,869
Well, your son called.

256
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:12,205
He said he has a complicated situation.

257
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:14,583
He got involved with a woman.

258
00:22:14,666 --> 00:22:17,878
We're going to be grandparents.

259
00:22:18,795 --> 00:22:19,838
Mikoy!

260
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:22,215
That's not a complicated situation.

261
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:26,678
Actually, if you think about it,
children are truly a blessing.

262
00:22:26,762 --> 00:22:28,555
The important thing
is you take responsibility.

263
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:31,725
You know in the Pinagpala family,
no one runs away

264
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:33,727
from their responsibilities.

265
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:35,228
And don't worry,

266
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:37,856
we'll help you raise the kids.

267
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:40,984
Mom! Dad! Wait a minute!

268
00:22:41,068 --> 00:22:43,070
You're going the wrong way.

269
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:44,321
No one got pregnant!

270
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:46,406
I didn't get anyone pregnant,
nothing like that.

271
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:50,410
Then what is this
complicated situation you got into?

272
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,829
It's just that I met a girl.

273
00:22:52,913 --> 00:22:53,997
And then?

274
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:57,375
Well, we kind of got serious.

275
00:22:57,459 --> 00:22:59,669
There! Kaboom!

276
00:23:00,962 --> 00:23:03,173
But she comes from a rich family, Dad.

277
00:23:03,256 --> 00:23:05,300
And she's not just rich.

278
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:08,887
She's the daughter of one
of the richest families here in Prague.

279
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:09,805
That level!

280
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:13,600
Son, that's what you call a jackpot.

281
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,603
That's not a problem!

282
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:19,189
Stop it. Wait a minute.

283
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:20,982
Why?

284
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,068
Is her family snobbish?

285
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:26,238
Okay, hold on.

286
00:23:26,321 --> 00:23:27,405
Tell me.

287
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:29,866
How's her attitude?

288
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:31,576
"You buy me this." "You buy me that."

289
00:23:32,327 --> 00:23:34,121
Not really, Dad.

290
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:36,373
Actually, she's just simple.

291
00:23:36,873 --> 00:23:38,208
She's fun to be with.

292
00:23:38,291 --> 00:23:39,709
She's easygoing.

293
00:23:39,793 --> 00:23:40,919
And she drinks a lot!

294
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,671
-So, what's the problem?
-Right.

295
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:44,673
Well, Mom,

296
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:47,092
even if you turn the world upside down,

297
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:49,970
we're not meant for each other.

298
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:52,180
She's like heaven!

299
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:53,682
And me,

300
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:56,393
I'm probably lower than the ground.

301
00:23:56,893 --> 00:23:57,853
Like dirt.

302
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:00,313
You're putting yourself down too much.

303
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:02,357
Not really, Dad. But…

304
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:03,567
But what?

305
00:24:03,650 --> 00:24:05,986
But I'm just being honest.

306
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:11,241
Because the poor don't usually end up
with the wealthy elite.

307
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:14,703
Son, I disagree with you.

308
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:16,413
You know this still happens.

309
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,874
The rich falls in love with the poor.

310
00:24:18,957 --> 00:24:20,333
-It can happen.
-Yes.

311
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:23,587
Do you know any poor people
who ended up with the rich?

312
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:26,256
Tenten and Serena!

313
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:27,382
Huh?

314
00:24:27,465 --> 00:24:28,717
Exactly, Mom.

315
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,760
It only happens on TV dramas.

316
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:31,928
Mikoy,

317
00:24:32,762 --> 00:24:33,930
listen to me, okay?

318
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:37,225
Your worth is not measured by money.

319
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,394
Your worth is measured

320
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,897
by the depth of your heart.

321
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:46,109
The most important thing

322
00:24:47,861 --> 00:24:49,779
is what you value the most.

323
00:24:52,449 --> 00:24:53,283
Exactly!

324
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:57,037
Okay, Mom and Dad.

325
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,455
I love you.

326
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:00,707
I'll rest now.

327
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:57,430
This is Vicek, Hrobnik, and Pes.

328
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:58,700
CZECH CABLE COMPANY

329
00:26:58,783 --> 00:27:01,703
The fact that Chiara
is still reaching out to Mikoy,

330
00:27:02,203 --> 00:27:05,665
it means we still have a chance
to infiltrate the Moraviano Syndicate.

331
00:27:05,749 --> 00:27:08,668
I really don't know
what she sees in Mikoy.

332
00:27:09,377 --> 00:27:10,754
Look, he's just fair-skinned.

333
00:27:10,837 --> 00:27:12,339
He has no sex appeal.

334
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:17,677
Looks like the Valtrovi's
only daughter got hit hard.

335
00:27:19,095 --> 00:27:21,097
Stay here. I'll follow them.

336
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:23,725
Okay.

337
00:27:25,226 --> 00:27:26,311
Wait!

338
00:27:28,188 --> 00:27:30,523
Hey, buddy! Keep your channel open.

339
00:27:44,037 --> 00:27:46,039
I hope you understand my fears.

340
00:27:47,957 --> 00:27:49,667
I have fears, too.

341
00:27:54,631 --> 00:27:56,299
If it's okay with you,

342
00:27:56,383 --> 00:27:58,218
I'm ready to make it work.

343
00:28:01,805 --> 00:28:04,599
Mr. Mikoy D. Pinagpala.

344
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:29,624
Is it okay that I already
introduced you to Mom and Dad?

345
00:28:29,707 --> 00:28:31,292
It's not a problem.

346
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:32,627
I don't understand them.

347
00:28:32,710 --> 00:28:35,630
My mom and dad don't trust people easily.

348
00:28:35,713 --> 00:28:37,549
They have many enemies.

349
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:45,223
We are not the bad guys here, Mikoy.

350
00:28:45,306 --> 00:28:46,766
Why should I believe you?

351
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:48,935
You might actually be the syndicate.

352
00:28:49,018 --> 00:28:50,061
You already know what to do.
